SNAP Recipients

Percent of SNAP Recipients by State

This map shows SNAP recipients by state as a percent of state population estimates. Both SNAP recipient counts and state population estimates are as of January 2020. The darker states on the map have a higher percentage of SNAP recipients.

state_pop <-
  read.csv("/Users/armellecoutant/Documents/GitHub/218z/covid19_food_assistance/state_pop.csv")

snap_pop <-
  read.csv("/Users/armellecoutant/Documents/GitHub/218z/covid19_food_assistance/snap_pop.csv")

snap_by_state <-
  left_join(state_pop, snap_pop, by = c("STATE" = "STATE"))

snap_by_state <-
  snap_by_state %>%
  mutate(
    "%" =(SNAP/POPULATION)*100,
  )

snap_by_state <-
  snap_by_state %>%
  inner_join(state_laea, by = c("STATE" = "STATE")) %>%
  st_as_sf()

tm_shape(snap_by_state) +
tm_polygons(col = "%", legend.hist = TRUE, border.col = "white") +
tm_layout(main.title = "Percent of State Population on SNAP Benefits (Jan, 2020)", main.title.size = 1, legend.outside = TRUE, legend.title.color = "white", legend.title.size = 0.0001, legend.hist.width = 1)
